thia are watching along, and no one is holding back.\n| LineColor       = 689CCF\n}}\n}}\n\n==''90 Day Fianc\u00e9: The Other Way''==\n\nIn May 2019, a spin-off titled ''90 Day Fianc\u00e9: The Other Way'' was announced, which premiered on June 3, 2019. This spin-off is dedicated to couples where the American partner marries their partner abroad and permanently moves to their partner's home country.<ref>{{cite web|title=A Reason to Look Forward to Mondays! TLC's New Series \"90 Day Fiance: The Other Way\" Premieres Monday, June 3 at 9PM ET/PT|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/05/06/a-reason-to-look-forward-to-mondays-tlcs-new-series-90-day-fiance-the-other-way-premieres-monday-june-3-at-9pm-et-pt-557110/20190506tlc01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=May 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Season 1 ===\nThe first season follows the stories of six couples - Jenny from [[Palm Springs, California]] & Sumit from [[New Delhi]], [[India]]; Laura from [[Eustis, Florida]] (originally from [[Canada]]) & Aladin from [[Doha]], [[Qatar]] (originally from [[Tunisia]]); Tiffany from [[Frederick, Maryland]] & Ronald from [[Randfontein]], [[South Africa]]; Corey from Mill A, [[Washington (state)|Washington]] and Evelin from Engabao, [[Ecuador]]; Deavan from [[Salt Lake City|Salt Lake City, Utah]] & Jihoon from [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]; and ''90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Before the 90 Days'' season one and two cast members, Paul from [[Louisville, Kentucky]] & Karine from [[Tonantins]], [[Brazil]]. <!--Summaries of episodes not finished, will finish later; feel free to change any grammatical errors or add any details that you feel should be included-->{{Episode table |background=#B30713 |overall=1 |season=1 |title=65 |airdate=25 |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = All in the Name of Love\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|06|03}}\n| ShortSummary    = Jenny tells her daughter about how the relationship started with Sumit catfishing her, but eventually telling her the truth. She also got her visa which allows her to enter India. Tiffany tells the story of her son's birth and how her relationship with Ronald started. Ronald also provides background context for his gambling addiction and shows his rehabilitation process. Corey tells the story of his relationship with Evelin, and confront her about their life-savings for his move to Ecuador. They also both confront Corey's parents about their future together. Paul recaps their relationship since the first season of ''90 Day Fiance: Before the 90 Days'', including details about how they met, a miscarriage, a second pregnancy, and the ups and downs of their relationship.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = Embargos and Ultimatums\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|06|03}}\n| ShortSummary    = Evelin, during a trip in her partner's hometown, gives Corey a life-changing ultimatum\u2014the only way she will pursue their relationship is if he permanently moves to her home country, Ecuador. Ronald's gambling addiction worries Tiffany's family about her relationship with him; and after meeting with an immigration lawyer, she realizes that it would be hard for Ronald to move to the United States due to his past criminal charges, and is now considering of moving to South Africa. Sumit's friends are skeptical of Sumit's plans to marry Jenny, due to traditional marriage customs in India. Jenny's friends are also skeptical because of how she will fit into a new culture-shocking country. Paul learns that due to an embargo, he cannot bring more than two bags to Brazil, which led him to cancel his flight.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = It's Go Time\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|06|10}}\n| ShortSummary    = Jenny spent her final moments with her family, and arrived in India. She felt paranoid due to Sumit not arriving on time to pick her up for the reason being that before she arrived, he had to confront his parents about moving out of their house. Paul confronts Karine about cancelling his flight due to an embargo. Later, with the help of his airline, Paul rebooked another flight and said his goodbyes to his mother. Corey addresses his decision to move to a different country to be with his partner, Evelin, to his parents. He also overcomes his [[trypanophobia]] (fear of needles) during a vaccination appointment to prepare him for Ecuador.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = Big Expectations\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|06|17}}\n| ShortSummary    = An hour after Jenny arrived in India, Sumit finally picked her up from the airport and they get settled in their new apartment. Karine talks about Paul to her brother, who doesn't seem to have good impressions of him. Paul later arrives in Brazil, surprising Karine, who didn't expect his arrival. Tiffany speaks with a friend about her plan to move to South Africa and how it might affect her son and herself. Days later, she said her goodbyes and left the States. Laura discusses the future of her relationship with a close friend.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| Title           = No Looking Back\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|06|24}}\n| ShortSummary    = After arriving in South Africa, Tiffany and her son were welcomed by Ronald's mother. The next day, Ronald meets her son for the first time. Before leaving the Wellness Center, the director gave the couple a warning about his addiction and how it may lead to another problem, if overlooked. Corey develops doubts about the future of his relationship with Evelin, after he talked with her over a video chat. Later, Corey arrives in Ecuador, not expecting to go to Engabao\u2014Evelin's hometown\u2014on his own. Jihoon and Deavan separately give an introduction to their lives and they both describe how they met each other online. Deavan also talks about her plans of immigrating to South Korea. Jihoon confronts his parents about the future of their relationship. Sumit and Jenny roam the streets of India, and she is faced with the challenge of adapting to Indian culture.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = Another World\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|07|01}}\n| ShortSummary    = Corey deals with culture shocks. Deavan meets Jihoon's parents for the first time. Laura visits a sex shop in the hopes of spicing up her and Aladin's sex life. Paul receives bad news about his request of permanent residency in Brazil.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| Title           = Broken Promises\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|07|08}}\n| ShortSummary    = Tiffany sets rules for Ronald's bachelor party. Paul seeks legal advise after receiving a deportation notice. Laura has second thoughts about leaving. Deavan tries to impress Jihoon's parents with a homecooked breakfast. \n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = Chickening Out\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|07|15}}\n| ShortSummary    = Laura arrives in Qatar. Tiffany confronts Ronald about his bachelor party. Deavan takes Jihoon's parents on a tour around Las Vegas. Corey tries to make a good impression with Evelin's family. Jenny and Sumit learn about the difficulties of getting married in India.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 9\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n| Title           = Ripped Apart\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|07|22}}\n| ShortSummary    = Tiffany's son expresses doubts about living in South Africa. Sumit is forced to go back to his parents. Paul and Karine make their way to Karine's home town. Jihoon's proposal does not go as planned. Evelin kicks out Corey after a fight.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 10\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n| Title           = Rolling the Dice\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|07|29}}\n| ShortSummary    = Ronald has to resist temptation while picking up Tiffany's dad at a Casino hotel. Laura's sex toys offend Aladin. Corey and Evelin talk future. Paul tells Karine's parents about his legal problems of getting granted residency in Brazil. Sumit leaves Jenny to go home to his family.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 11\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n| Title           = Blind Trust\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|05}}\n| ShortSummary    = Tiffany and Ronald get married. Deavan tells Jihoon about having to get the baby out early. Laura learns more about Aladin. Paul accuses Karine of talking to other men online. Corey tries to get used to Evelins past.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 12\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n| Title           = Baby, Come Back\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|12}}\n| ShortSummary    = Jenny tries to get by without Sumit. Deavan gives birth. Tiffany is shocked about their possible living situation in South Africa and worries about safety. Karine is concerned about Paul not being able to take care of them financially once the baby comes.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 13\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n| Title           = Breaking Point\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|19}}\n| ShortSummary    = Jenny and Sumit get surprise visitors from the US. Karine finally has enough of Paul and plans to leave him. Corey discovers about Evelin's history with her ex. Deavan is worried if Jihoon can support their new family. Laura feels homesick.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 14\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 14\n| Title           = The Great Unknown\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|26}}\n| ShortSummary    = Tiffany and Ronald tell everyone about the baby news. Laura begs her son to attend her wedding. Deavan moves to South Korea. Corey asks Evelin to cut ties with her ex. Karine and her mom leave Paul behind.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 15\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 15\n| Title           = Walking A Tight Rope\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|02}}\n| ShortSummary    = Deavan arrives in South Korea. Tiffany and Ronald have their first fight as a married couple. Paul tries to win back Karine before she goes into labor. Corey finds out about the unexpected passing of his dad. Jenny's daughter confronts Sumit.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 16\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 16\n| Title           = Fool's Gold\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|09}}\n| ShortSummary    = Jihoon opens up about his past. Jenny and Sumit's relationship reaches boiling point. Paul and Karine become parents. Laura's son arrives in Tunisia to attend the traditional three day wedding.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 17\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 17\n| Title           = Shattered Dreams\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|16}}\n| ShortSummary    = Jenny is devastated after Sumit's family busted into their apartment. Laura is torn between her son and Aladin. Corey thinks about whether to go back to Ecuador or support his mom in the US. Paul's mother visits Karine and Paul in Brazil. Tiffany is terrified about giving birth in South Africa after checking out possible hospitals.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 18\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 18\n| Title           = Torn\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|23}}\n| ShortSummary    = Sumit confesses that he is already married. Deavon discovers the reason for Jihoon's financial problems. Corey returns to Ecuador with three weeks left on his visa before he has to marry Evelin or leave the country. Laura's son forbids Aladin to have children with Laura.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 19\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 19\n| Title           = Falling Apart\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|30}}\n| ShortSummary    = Jenny and Sumit see each other for the first time after she found out he's married. Laura's son apologizes for his behavior and finally attends the third day of Laura's and Aladin's wedding. Paul's mother gets ready to leave Brazil but tries to reason with his son before she does. Tiffany decides to leave South Africa and try to apply for Ronald's spousal visa to the US. \n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 20\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 20\n| Title           = Never Let Me Go\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|07}}\n| ShortSummary    = After Sumit is forced to go back to his wife, Jenny decides to leave India. Deavan gets used to Korean culture in a traditional Korean wedding ceremony. Corey asks Evelyn's dad for his blessing and proposes to Evelyn after a hot air balloon ride. Tiffany and her son go back to the US leaving behind a devastated Ronald.  \n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 21\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 21\n| Title           = Tell All: Part 1\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|14}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 22\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 22\n| Title           = Tell All: Part 2\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|21}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n}}\n\n==''The Family Chantel''==\n\nOn April 9, 2019, a new spin-off titled ''The Family Chantel'' was announced, which is centered on the relationship of ''90 Day Fianc\u00e9'' season four cast members' Pedro and Chantel Jimeno and their immediate family.<ref>{{cite web|title=TLC to Debut New Series \"The Family Chantel,\" A Spinoff from the \"90 Day Fiance\" Franchise|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/04/08/tlc-to-debut-new-series-the-family-chantel-a-spinoff-from-the-90-day-fiance-franchise-671301/20190408tlc01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=April 9, 2019}}</ref> The series premiered on July 22, 2019.<ref name=\"90 Day Fianc\u00e9 2019 News\">{{cite web|title=TLC's Sizzling Summer Lineup Brings the Heat with Series Premiere of \"The Family Chantel\" and Return of \"Before the 90 Days\"|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/06/24/tlcs-sizzling-summer-lineup-brings-the-heat-with-series-premiere-of-the-family-chantel-and-return-of-before-the-90-days-37112/20190624tlc01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=June 24, 2019}}</ref>{{Episode table |background=#B30713 |overall=1 |season=1 |title=65 |airdate=25 |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = All's Fair in Love and War\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|07|22}}\n| ShortSummary    = Chantel confronts Pedro after revealing what she learned from her trip to the Dominican Republic; the family's pastor encourages the couple to seek family counseling while Pedro and his sister discuss a secret plan.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = How to Come to America\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|07|29}}\n| ShortSummary    = Pedro and Chantel's family attend a family counseling session; Chantel confronts Pedro after learning about his secret plans.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = The Truth Comes Out\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|05}}\n| ShortSummary    = Chantel confronts Pedro about his secret plan; Karen hires a private investigator to check on Winter's secretive boyfriend; Thomas tries to convince Pedro to join him for a guy's weekend.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = It's All Crashing Down\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|12}}\n| ShortSummary    = The private investigator returns with some shocking news for Jah, Chantel and Karen; Thomas, Pedro and River spend the night on a dude ranch and are forced to face their issues head-on.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| Title           = Pack Your Bags\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|19}}\n| ShortSummary    = Pedro's sister reveals their aging grandma is sick, so Chantel joins him on the trip to the Dominican Republic; the Family Chantel joins the trip to keep Chantel safe.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = The Fight to Get Along\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|26}}\n| ShortSummary    = Chantel's family joins Pedro and Chantel in the Dominican Republic; both families get together for a face-off.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| Title           = The Last Supper\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|02}}\n| ShortSummary    = After a tense exchange, Chantel and Pedro form a plan to bring their feuding families together; Chantel confronts Pedro's mother about the problems she's caused in her marriage; Pedro goes head to head with Obed to finally find out the truth.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = What Are Your Intentions?\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|09}}\n| ShortSummary    = Chantel's family members come to a surprising decision about visiting Pedro's family; tensions rise after the local cuisine is once again refused; Chantel confronts Coraima and hurls more than insults.\n| LineColor       = B30713\n}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{TLC Programming}}\n\n[[Category:2010s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:2014 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in North America]]\n[[Category:TLC (TV network) original programming]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|US television series}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Update|type=|date=August 2019|reason=The sections about The Family Chantel and 90 Day Fiance: The Other Way show information that is not up to date with the current line of events. The section about The Family Chantel dates back prior to the premiere of The Family Chantel. The list of characters is not up to date with the show, and needs to be updated. Other sections may require updating as well.}}\n{{cleanup|reason=length; not appropriate to include children's names|date=April 2019}}\n}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = 90 Day Fianc\u00e9\n| image                    = 90_Day_Fiance_logo.jpg\n| genre                    = [[Reality television]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 7\n| num_episodes             = 79\n| company                  = [[Sharp Entertainment]]\n| network                  = [[TLC (TV network)|TLC]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2014|01|12}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|present }}\n| related                  = <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations --> ''[[#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Happily Ever After?|90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Happily Ever After?]]<br>[[#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Before the 90 Days|90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Before the 90 Days]]<br>[[#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: What Now?|90 Day Fianc\u00e9: What Now?]]<br>[[#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Pillow Talk|90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Pillow Talk]]<br>[[#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: The Other Way|90 Day Fianc\u00e9: The Other Way]]<br>[[#The Family Chantel|The Family Chantel]]''\n| website                  = http://www.tlc.com/tv-shows/90-day-fiance/\n| website_title            = tlc.com\n| image_size               = 240px\n}}\n'''''90 Day Fianc\u00e9 '''''is an [[United States|American]] [[documentary series|documentary]]/[[reality television|reality TV series]] on [[TLC (TV network)|TLC]] that follows couples who have applied for or received a [[K-1 visa]] (available uniquely to foreign fianc\u00e9s of U.S. citizens) and therefore have ninety days to marry each other. The purpose of the K-1 Visa is to allow time for the couple to make arrangements for and actually have the marriage ceremony.  The visa is not to give the couple time \"to decide IF\" they will marry. Each couple has already signed document(s) stating that they have promised to marry each other, and provided the signed document(s) to the US Immigration services to get the K-1 Visa. \n\nThe series debuted on January 12, 2014, and has been renewed through its seventh season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/tv/a27214674/90-day-fiance-season-7-news-cast-spoilers/|title=When Is a New Season of \u201890 Day Fianc\u00e9\u2019 Coming?|last=Beck|first=Laura|date=2019-04-25|website=Cosmopolitan|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-11}}</ref>\n\nThe series currently has six spin-offs: ''[[90 Day Fianc\u00e9#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Happily Ever After?|90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Happily Ever After]]'', which documents the ups and downs of past ''90 Day Fianc\u00e9'' couples after their marriage; ''[[90 Day Fianc\u00e9#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Happily Ever After?|90 Day Fianc\u00e9]]: Before the 90 Days,'' which follows couples that have met each other online, but have not yet started the K-1 visa process; ''[[90 Day Fianc\u00e9#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: What Now?|90 Day Fianc\u00e9: What Now?]],'' an original digital series that gives updates on past 90 Day Fianc\u00e9 couples; ''[[90 Day Fianc\u00e9#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: The Other Way|90 Day Fianc\u00e9: The Other Way]],'' a dedicated series to couples where the American partner permanently moves into their partner's home country instead of the foreign partner doing so; ''[[90 Day Fianc\u00e9#90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Pillow Talk|90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Pillow Talk]],'' a reaction show featuring a number of previous cast members that take part in reacting to an episode of ''90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Happily Ever After; and [[90 Day Fianc\u00e9#The Family Chantel|The Family Chantel]],'' focused on the relationship of ''90 Day Fianc\u00e9'' season four cast members Pedro and Chantel, and their immediate family.\n\n==''K-1 visa process''==\n{{Main|K-1 visa}}\nThe show is based on the K-1 visa process, which begins with the petitioner meeting the beneficiary inside or outside the United States, then filing a I-129F petition with evidence of meeting and of a relationship. After the petition is approved, the petitioner must pass biometrics and then the process is sent to the foreign embassy of the beneficiary. The beneficiary then files for a visa, before or after passing the medical requirements and is called for an interview, in which the beneficiary must prove that they meet the requirements of the visa, including having strong evidence of meeting and a valid relationship. If approved, the foreign fianc\u00e9 travels to the States to live with his or her prospective American spouse. The couple must marry within 90 days, otherwise the beneficiary must leave the country. The couple may face language barriers, culture shock, the stigma of being thought of as a \"[[mail-order bride]]\" as well as skepticism of friends and family.  Professor Lenni B. Benson of the New York Law School has stated that  although the K-1 visa program is widely associated with [[sham marriage]]s, \"It is not true in the majority of cases.\"  <ref>{{cite news |title=\u201890 Day Fianc\u00e9\u2019: An Anti-Fantasy for Troubled Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/15/arts/television/90-day-fiance-immigration.html |accessdate=20 August 2019 |publisher=New York Times}}</ref>\n\n==Season 1 cast==\n\n===Russ & Paola===\nRuss Mayfield (27, from [[Owasso, Oklahoma]]) met Paola \"Pao\" (26, from [[Bucaramanga]], [[Colombia]]), a fashion designer, while he was in Colombia on a work assignment in the [[petroleum industry]]. They married and moved to [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]]. Russ is a graduate of [[Oklahoma State University\u2013Stillwater]] and works as a field engineer, although he lost his job shortly after marrying. Paola then moved to [[Miami]] to seek more opportunities modeling and as a personal trainer and for its larger Latin community, while Russ initially remains in Oklahoma City. Eventually, Russ moves to Miami, but is concerned about Pao's skimpy outfits during her modeling jobs. Paola advanced to the second round of the 2017 [[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'s Finest competition, but was eventually eliminated. In 2018 they announced they were expecting their first child, a boy. Russ and Paola Mayfield welcomed their son whom they named Axel on January 1, 2019.\n\n===Alan & Kirlyam===\nAlan Cox (29, from [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]) met Kirlyam (21, from [[Goi\u00e2nia]], [[Brazil]]) while he was on a [[Mormon]] mission to her hometown. She moved to the United States to live with him, although the two were [[virgin]]s at the time of their wedding. She tried modeling, but Alan was jealous of the attention that she received. They were married in a Mormon [[Temple (Latter Day Saints)|temple]], and although Kirlyam's family was unable to attend, they watched a [[live streaming]] video of the event from Brazil. The couple went to [[Hawaii]] for their [[honeymoon]].\n\nKirlyam is waiting for her [[Permanent residence (United States)|green card]] so that she can find employment. Alan is employed by Breen Engineering as a project lead/photo simulation specialist. They are still together and in October 2017 Kirlyam gave birth to the couple's first child, a son named Liam.{{citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n\n===Louis & Aya===\nLouis Roy Gattone, Jr. (33, from [[Indianapolis]], [[Indiana]]) met Aya (30, from [[Ormoc]], [[Philippines]]), via an [[online dating service]]. Aya wanted Louis to move to the Philippines, but they decided to live in the United States because he has two young sons. They were married in a Catholic church. Louis is taking classes and is almost done with his degree. Aya is working. They plan to buy a house in the near future. The boys live with them and they plan on having a child or children of their own. The couple decided not to participate in the season 2 update. They are still married.\n\nIn February 2018 they announced they were expecting a baby boy. In June 2018 they welcomed their first child.\n\n===Mike & Aziza===\nMike Eloshway (31, from [[Cleveland]], [[Ohio]]) and Aziza (21, from [[Volgograd]], [[Russia]]) met on a [[language acquisition]] website. Their relationship was initially platonic. Sometime after Aziza's application for a work US visa was denied, their relationship turned romantic. In Summer 2014, she arrived to America to live with Mike. They were married although Aziza was very saddened because her family was unable to attend the wedding. Mike is employed as a technical support specialist for the Cleveland Municipal Court. Mike wants to have children right away, while Aziza does not. Aziza found employment at an optics lab. The couple traveled to Russia where Mike met Aziza's parents. Aziza gave birth to the couple's first child, a daughter Olivia Joan on January 14, 2019.{{citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n\n==Season 2 cast==\n\n===Chelsea & Yamir===\nYamir Castillo (28, from [[Managua]], [[Nicaragua]]) and Chelsea Macek (25, from [[Galesburg, Illinois]]) met while she was volunteering in Nicaragua. Yamir was a member of a Nicaraguan [[boy band]]. He moved to the United States to live with Chelsea and her parents. This caused a large rift between him and the members of his band. Chelsea's parents are very supportive of the relationship. Yamir sends some demo tapes to a few music producers in Chicago and receives a reply. He travels to [[Chicago]] to meet with producers. The producers say that he needs to move to Chicago to have better opportunities. Unfortunately, Chelsea is resistant to the idea because neither is employed and they can live for free with her parents in Galesburg. Yamir made his music debut in the United States with Chelsea playing his spouse in the music video, \"Party Love\". Chelsea found employment as an elementary school teacher. Yamir and Chelsea filed for divorce in 2017 and Yamir is still living in Chicago, working on his music. Yamir stated that \"Just because two people aren't together any longer doesn't mean you cannot have a relationship with that person. Although we no longer have the bond that united us, there's no hate!\"{{citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n\n===Danielle & Mohamed===\nMohamed Jbali, (26, from [[Tunis]], [[Tunisia]]), met Danielle Mullins (41, from [[Norwalk, Ohio]]) in an online chat room. The two were engaged, and Mohamed moved to Ohio. Danielle had 3 teenage daughters and 1 adult son from previous relationships. Mohamed claimed to have a job, but Danielle discovered that it was a lie. Mohamed also found out that Danielle had lied about aspects of her private life including passing bad checks and using someone else's credit card fraudulently. Shortly after the wedding, Mohamed left Danielle. He went to Florida with a female friend, and Danielle saw intimate photos of them on social media and consulted a lawyer. She filed for an [[annulment]], or a retroactive cancellation of the marriage which, if granted, would mean that Mohamed would be deported. In court Mohamed said he would fight the annulment and the judge stated it would be difficult for Danielle to win; Danielle's lawyer advised her to change the filing, and she removed the annulment.<ref>{{cite website |website=YouTube |title=What Happened At Danielle And Mohamed's Court Date? |url=http://www.election.demon.co.uk/by1992.html }}</ref> They divorced, and, in October 2017, Mohamed moved to [[Texas]]. Danielle is still trying to get Mohamed deported, despite pleas from fellow cast members and fans to \"let it go.\"{{citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n\n===Justin & Evelin===\nJustin (34, from [[San Jose, California]]) and Evelin (29, from [[Cali]], Colombia) met while they were both attending a rugby match at the [[2013 World Games]] in Colombia. After their first night together, Justin told Evelin to vacuum and clean the dishes, while he watched a football game. They spent the following 7 days together and fell in love. Justin works as a physical education teacher at an elementary school. In Colombia, Evelin worked as a dance instructor. The couple struggled with Justin's family, as Justin had not told them he was dating anyone until he and Evelin were engaged, causing some relatives to question Evelin's intentions. However, Evelin ended up becoming close to Justin's family, especially his mom. Since moving to the United States, Evelin has changed the spelling of her name to Evelyn. They are still married.\n\n===Brett & Daya===\nBrett Otto (31, from [[Snohomish, Washington]]) and Daya De Arce (29, from [[San Carlos, Negros Occidental]], [[Philippines]]) met via an [[online dating service]]. Brett was divorced and has a 6-year-old daughter from his first marriage. His daughter lives with her mother in [[Montana]]. Brett works in tool services for [[Boeing]], and Daya found a job in the United States. He had two roommates, but Brett and Daya moved out into their own apartment. Brett and Daya were married on February 14, 2015. Brett's mother chose not to attend the wedding.\n\nThey are still married and welcomed a daughter named Isabelle in July 2017.\n\n===Jason & C\u00e1ssia===\nJason Hitch (38, from [[Spring Hill, Florida]]) and C\u00e1ssia Tavares (23, from [[Curitiba]], [[Brazil]]) met through [[Facebook]] while C\u00e1ssia was in an online relationship with Jason's friend. Once that relationship ended, Jason and C\u00e1ssia began dating. C\u00e1ssia came to the United States and moved in with Jason and his father. Jason is originally from [[Champaign, Illinois]], and is a [[United States Army]] veteran. He lives very frugally. He buys items from garage sales, auctions, and estate sales, and sells them online for a profit. They started a mail-order snack business called \"Gifting Fun\". In 2017, they separated. In 2018, they filed for divorce after Jason was charged with [[Domestic violence#Physical|domestic violence]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://radaronline.com/videos/90-day-fiance-jason-hitch-cassia-tavares-divorce/|title='90 Day Fianc\u00e9's Jason Tells All On Divorce From Cassia: \u2018She Resented Everything!'|date=12 January 2018|publisher=}}</ref> In April 2018, they dismissed their divorce case and are working on their marriage. In September 2018, Jason filed for divorce.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.intouchweekly.com/posts/90-day-fiance-jason-cassia-call-off-divorce-157212|title='90 Day Fianc\u00e9' Stars Jason Hitch and Cassia Tavares Call off Their Divorce (REPORT)|date=2018-04-01|work=In Touch Weekly|access-date=2018-05-20}}</ref>  The couple officially divorced in October 2018.\n\n===Danny & Amy===\nDanny Frishmuth (23, from [[Norristown, Pennsylvania]]), and Amy (21, from [[Cape Town]], [[South Africa]]) met in [[Australia]] while they were on a [[Bible]] [[Mission trip|study trip]]. They fell in love and got engaged. When Amy arrived in America, she lived with Danny's brother because she and Danny wanted to be virgins when they wed. Danny works in home construction for X-Treme Works in [[Malvern, Pennsylvania]]. Danny's father initially objected to the marriage because Amy is not white, but he eventually accepted her into the family. They were married in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/90-day-fiance-couple-danny-and-amy-frishmuth-pregnant-with-first-child-2015155/|title=90 Day Fiance Couple Danny and Amy Frishmuth Pregnant With First Child!|date=15 May 2015|publisher=}}</ref> They are still married and are now living in [[Texas]]. They have one son Jedidiah (born in June 2015) and a daughter Anna (born in July 2017).\n\n==Season 3 cast==\n\n===Mark & Nikki===\nMark (58, from [[Baltimore]], [[Maryland]]) and Nikki (19, from [[Cebu City]], Philippines) met via an [[online dating service]]. Mark owns a concert piano rental business. He has 4 adult children from a previous marriage who are all older than Nikki. He and his first wife's relationship ended when the children were very young, and Mark was left to raise the children. Mark's first wife and Nikki are both from Cebu, Philippines. Shortly after meeting Nikki, Mark proposed to her. When Nikki came to Maryland, Mark surprised her with a car and taught her how to drive. The car was the same make and model that Mark gave to his first wife. He demanded that Nikki sign a [[prenuptial agreement]]. Mark's daughter, Elise, felt uncomfortable with the relationship because she is a year older than Nikki. Elise shared her discomfort when Mark wanted to give Nikki clothes that she had previously discarded. The couple sued TLC for broken written promises, including: that the \"show is a documentary, not scripted, not staged, filmed as it happens\" and \"you are not forced to do or say anything.\"   However, the lawsuit was eventually dismissed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.intouchweekly.com/posts/90-day-fiance-mark-nikki-lawsuit-148213/|title=90 Day Fianc\u00e9 Stars Mark and Nikki Shoemaker Lose Lawsuit Against TLC|date=4 December 2017|publisher=}}</ref> They couple do not have any active social media and it is unknown if they are still married.\n\n===Loren & Alexei===\nAlexei Brovarnik (27, from [[Nazareth Illit]], [[Israel]], originally from Ukraine) and Loren Goldstone (27, from [[New York City]]), met while she was on a [[Birthright Israel]] trip, where he was a medic. Loren was an [[executive assistant]] in New York, but she quit and moved to [[Parkland, Florida]] to save money. Loren admits to liking expensive things, but claims she is not a [[spoiled child]]. She is a graduate of the [[University of North Florida]]. In addition to marrying in the United States, Alexei and Loren got married in Israel, surrounded by Alexei's family and friends and Loren's parents. Loren wants Alexei to be a model, while he wants to be a firefighter, paramedic, or policeman. Soon after they are married Alexei's mom travels to Florida to explore ways to move the whole family from Israel to the United States. The couple is still together and resides in [[Fort Lauderdale, Florida]]. On October 29, 2019, the couple announced that Loren is pregnant with their first child, and is expected to give birth to a son in May 2020. \nAlexei was approved for his US citizenship in January of 2020.\n\n===Kyle & Noon===\nKyle Huckabee (28, from [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]]) and Bajaree Boonma aka Noon (25, from [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]) met online through [[Facebook]] while he was doing research for a trip to Thailand. The two met in person while he was there on vacation. They were engaged and Noon came to America even though Kyle hadn't officially proposed. They initially lived in Kyle's bachelor apartment with his roommate, but the situation was less than ideal. Kyle started working extra shifts at his job as a bartender on [[Bourbon Street]] so that they could afford an apartment of their own. Kyle proposed during a [[parachuting]] trip, and they moved into a new apartment. Before he met Noon, Kyle was estranged from his parents who are divorced. With Noon's support, he restarted the relationship with his mother. Kyle & Noon were married in a Buddhist temple, but unfortunately, Noon's family were unable to attend the ceremony. Kyle's mom chose not to attend. They are still married.\n\n===Melanie & Devar===\nDevar Walters (28, from [[Runaway Bay, Jamaica]]) and Melanie Bowers (33, from [[Orwigsburg, Pennsylvania]]) met while Melanie was on vacation at a Jamaican resort where Devar was employed as a lifeguard. Melanie is a registered nurse. She has custody of her 11-year-old son, Hunter, on weekends. She was married to his father for 5 years before the marriage ended in divorce when she was 26. Devar proposed to Melanie while she was still vacationing, and she accepted. Back in Pennsylvania, Melanie's sister, Bev, is extremely concerned and does not trust Devar. The couple hits a rough patch when Devar mentions he wants to send most of the money he earns to his family in Jamaica; Melanie ponders out loud that she will look into a [[prenuptial agreement]]. Devar has been training to become a welder.\n\nThey are still together and the couple has a daughter Avah who was born in November 2017.{{citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n\n===Fernando & Carolina===\nFernando (39, from [[Doral, Florida]]) and Carolina (22, from [[Medell\u00edn]], [[Colombia]]) met in Colombia while both were on dates with other people. The two were engaged before he returned to the United States. Fernando was previously married. After his marriage ended, Fernando invited his parents to share his house. When Carolina moves to Florida, Fernando's mom makes inappropriate remarks such as telling Carolina that all people from Colombia are [[cocaine]] addicts. Even though Carolina does not get along with Fernando's mom, they get married. The couple happily settled in together, though Carolina admits she calls her mom 3 times per day and misses her cat, while Fernando is allergic to cats. Fernando gained 50 pounds since meeting Carolina. Fernando says he did not cheat, although Carolina found emails that he exchanged with an ex-girlfriend. They are still married.\n\n===Josh & Aleksandra===\nJosh Strobel (22, from [[Rexburg, Idaho]]) and Aleksandra Iarovikova (21, from [[Kirov, Kirov Oblast|Kirov]], Russia), met in [[Prague]], [[Czech Republic]], while Josh was on a [[Mormon]] [[Missionary (LDS Church)|mission]] and Aleksandra was attending [[Metropolitan University Prague]]. Initially an atheist, Aleksandra converted to Mormonism and Josh played a role in this. Before converting, she was also employed as a go-go dancer at a club and loved drinking and partying. The couple kept in touch after Josh's mission and began dating. Josh visited Russia and proposed in 2015.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00HTAQD00 | title=Amazon.com: 90 Day Fiance Season 1: Amazon Digital Services LLC | website=[[Amazon.com]]}}</ref> Josh and Aleksandra were married in August 2015, soon after Aleksandra's arrival to the United States from Prague, where she had to finalize her semester in June. They had a daughter named Kaya in March 2016. Their daughter looks biracial which caused a lot of controversy because both Aleksandra and Josh are white. \n \nJosh graduated with a BS from Creighton University in 2016, but was not accepted to a medical school that year and started working for his father. At the beginning of 2018, Josh started medical school at the [[University of Queensland]], in Australia, and the family moved to [[Brisbane]], [[Australia]]. In December 2018 the couple announced that they are expecting their second child.\n\n==Season 4 cast==\n\n===Jorge & Anfisa===\nAnfisa Arkhipchenko (20, from [[Moscow]], [[Russia]]) was contacted by Jorge Nava (27, from [[Riverside, California]]) via [[Facebook]] after he saw her photos online. Though Anfisa was at first resistant to his messages, Anfisa eventually agreed to meet him and the couple embarked on an expensive vacation around Europe. Shortly before Anfisa was scheduled to come to the United States, she asked Jorge for a $10,000 handbag, which Jorge declined to buy. Anfisa erased Jorge's cellphone and cancelled the flights. However, the two reconciled and Anfisa agreed to travel to the United States. Jorge pleaded guilty to marijuana trafficking, which made it hard for him to rent an apartment. They moved into a hotel and Anfisa was not impressed (though why exactly Jorge does not have his own place to live has not been revealed). They later moved into a small apartment. Jorge did not buy an engagement ring or wedding dress for Anfisa, and Jorge's friends and family became concerned about Anfisa's motives. Anfisa admitted that she was indeed interested in Jorge providing for her and stated that while she may be using Jorge for his money, Jorge is primarily interested in her for her looks and would not want to marry her if she was ugly. Anfisa considered returning to Russia, and Jorge considered not trying to stop her. They later got married alone in a simple courthouse ceremony, after which Jorge promised both to buy a ring for Anfisa and to hold a bigger ceremony her family could attend.\n\nJorge's sister confronted Anfisa at a restaurant about her demands. They remained living in a small apartment, Jorge did not buy Anfisa a ring.  Later they separated for a few months and Anfisa got a new apartment, driver's license and a car. Despite a bitter and hate-filled separation, Anfisa and Jorge are still married. In early 2018, Jorge was arrested for transporting 293 pounds of [[marijuana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/90-day-fiance-star-jorge-nava-to-spend-2-half-years-in-prison/|title=90 Day Fianc\u00e9 Star Jorge Nava to Spend 2.5 Years in Prison|website=PEOPLE.com}}</ref> In September 2018, Jorge was sentenced to 2.5 years in prison. The couple have since broken up, and Anfisa is dating a new man.\n\n===Nicole & Azan===\nNicole Nafziger (22, from [[Bradenton, Florida]]) and Azan Tefou (24, from [[Agadir]], [[Morocco]]), met via an [[online dating service]] [[mobile app]]. Though somewhat against her parents wishes, Nicole decides to go to Morocco for 5 weeks, leaving her toddler-aged daughter May with her sister. Upon meeting Nicole at the airport, Azan remarks that she is \"big...a little bit\" but concedes that he is happy. Nicole is thrilled to be in Morocco with Azan (later calling him her \"Arabian Prince\"), though he has a hard time persuading her that in his culture it is not acceptable for unmarried couples to be physically affectionate. Nicole persists in trying to hug and kiss Azan, which only causes him to become irritated. Nicole feels shunned and unsure of their relationship. Azan takes Nicole to [[Agadir]] to visit his family; she is warmly welcomed by the family. Nicole later reveals that she cheated on Azan, which could end the relationship. Azan takes Nicole to the desert and proposes, and she accepts. However, she continues to chafe at the customs of the [[Culture of Islam]]. She refuses to convert to [[Islam]] and he refuses to convert to [[Christianity]]. Their wedding is delayed indefinitely as Nicole does not earn enough money to sponsor Azan's visa, and her mother does not want to be a co-sponsor. Nicole believes it will take at least 2 years to save enough money and hopes Azan will wait. Their future is unsure, they are still together, but living in separate countries. In late 2017, Nicole's father agreed to sponsor Azan. They are featured again in season 5.\n\n===Narkyia & Olulowo===\nOlulowo (28, from [[Lagos]], [[Nigeria]]) met Narkyia (36, from [[Camp Hill, Pennsylvania]]) via an [[online dating service]] for [[overweight]] women. They faced many obstacles for meeting as he had previously lied about where he lived about his child's mother being dead. Narkyia and her friends and family were skeptical of him and are wary of a [[romance scam]], but he did not ask for any money. Narkyia went to Vietnam, where Lowo had previously lived, to meet him while he obtained some records needed for his K1 Visa. They broke up when Narkyia learned that Lowo had been trying to restart his relationship with his son's mother at the same time he started talking to her. At the end of the season, they were angry at each other and Narkyia was not optimistic about their future. After the show, however, they ended up getting married and now live in the United States. On March 25, 2020, Narkyia announced that she and Olulowo are pregnant with a daughter due in September.<ref>{{Cit web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-LhoeQDD4X/|title=Instagram Post from Narkyia Lathan-Shodipe|website=instagram.com}}</ref>\n\n===Matt & Alla===\nMatt Ryan (43, from [[Williamstown, Kentucky]]), and Alla Fedoruk (30, from [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]]), met several years ago using an [[online dating service]] but lost touch after Matt married his 3rd wife. A few years and a divorce later, Matt and Alla reconnected. Alla, also a divorcee, has a 7-year-old son named Max. The reserved Alla is easily overwhelmed by Matt's friends and family while Matt continues to deal with lingering issues caused by infidelity by his previous wives. Alla dreams of a wedding on the beach but Matt's family tries to persuade her to scale back her plans. When Alla says that she does not love Matt yet, his friends are very concerned. However, the couple marry. They are later shown looking for a new house, closer to city and Matt's family. In February 2020 the couple announced they are expecting a baby together.\n\n===Chantel & Pedro===\nChantel (real name: CeAir) Everett (25, from [[Atlanta, Georgia]]) met Pedro Jimeno (26, from [[Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic]]) while on a trip to the [[Dominican Republic]], after being introduced by a Spanish teacher. Chantel frequently went to the Dominican Republic to visit him, and on one of those trips he proposed to her. Chantel was worried that her family would think that Pedro was only going after a [[Permanent residence (United States)|green card]] to enter the U.S, so she told her parents that he was in America on a student [[travel visa]]. Eventually, Chantel and Pedro married in the United States, but they planned to marry in the Dominican Republic as well, although he didn't think her family would want to go. They did all go to the Dominican Republic, but explosive fights kept breaking out, since Pedro's family now expected him to send them money. Chantel's family was upset about the obvious improvement of Pedro's family's standard of living, while Chantel and Pedro lived very modestly in the United States. Pedro's family offered Chantel's family [[chicken feet]], which they took as a sign of disrespect. They did get married and reside in [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]. In July 2019, Chantel and Pedro's spinoff series \"The Family Chantel\" began airing on TLC.\n\n==Season 5 cast==\n\n===Elizabeth & Andrei===\nElizabeth Potthast (27, from [[Tampa, Florida]]), met Andrei Castravet (31, from [[Chisinau, Moldova]]), while Elizabeth visited [[Dublin]], where Andrei resided and worked as a [[Bouncer (doorman)|bouncer]]. At first, Andrei does not get along with Elizabeth's family due to his controlling nature and the haste of the marriage. Her family and friends express concerns that Andrei wants a submissive wife and that Elizabeth is being too accommodating to Andrei's wishes. Elizabeth's father refuses to financially support the couple, leading the couple to marry earlier so that Andrei can begin working sooner. \n\nElizabeth and her sisters go to [[Miami]] for a bachelorette party and they go clubbing, against Andrei's wishes. He catches her in a hotel committing sexual acts with multiple\nmen. She stated they were indeed in the act simultaneously. Andrei in the end forgives her. \n\nThe couple got married in an outdoor ceremony.On January 23, 2019, the couple welcomed their first child, a daughter named Eleanor Louise.\n\n===Evelyn & David===\nDavid V\u00e1zquez Zerme\u00f1o (27, from [[Granada, Spain]]) and Evelyn Cormier (18, from [[Claremont, New Hampshire]]), both from religious Christian families and both virgins before marriage, met after David saw the Facebook page for Evelyn's band<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.facebook.com/EvelynCormierMusic/ | title=Evelyn Cormier Music}}</ref> and sent her a message. They couple struggled with Evelyn's refusal to compromise on their wedding and David's refusal to discuss sex with Evelyn on camera. Despite David's objections to living in a small town, they got married and live in [[Claremont, New Hampshire]].\n\nIn February 2019, Evelyn  participated on the [[American Idol (season 17)|seventeenth season]] of ''[[American Idol]].'' In March 2019 it was announced that Evelyn made Final 20. She managed to make the Top 14 but was eliminated before the Top 10. {{citation needed|date=June 2019}} The couple are still married.\n\n===Molly & Luis===\nMolly Hopkins (41, from [[Woodstock, Georgia]]), met Luis Mendez (26, from [[Dominican Republic]]) at the bar he worked at while she was on a trip with friends to the [[Dominican Republic]].<ref name=waiting/>  Molly's oldest daughter was initially opposed to Luis moving in, and her father questioned Luis's intentions.\n\nThey did not have a wedding but did legally get married during the 90-day visa period. Luis did not get along with Molly's two children and was not interested in being a stepfather, and was generally bored and unsatisfied with his new life in Georgia. The couple argued about Luis's disinterest in wedding planning and Luis asking Molly's 17-year-old daughter questions about her sex life. He left Molly but later returned for the final episode, \"Tell All\".\n\nIn January 2018, after 6 months of being married, Molly filed for divorce while Luis claimed that he was emotionally and physically abused by her during their marriage.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.inquisitr.com/4817356/a-90-day-fiance-star-has-been-accused-of-domestic-violence/ | title=A \u201990 Day Fiance\u2019 Star Has Been Accused Of Domestic Violence | first=Bernadette | last=Giacomazzo | work=[[Inquisitr]] | date=March 7, 2018}}</ref> Five months after their divorce was finalized, Luis remarried in September 2018. He is now living in [[New Jersey]].\n\n===David & Annie===\nDavid Toborowsky (48, from [[Louisville, Kentucky]]), met Annie Suwan (24, from [[Bueng Kan]], [[Thailand]]) at a bar while he was living in [[Thailand]]. David has no money and relies on support from his best friend, [[Chris Thieneman]]. Chris sponsors Annie and gives David enough money to pay the [[bride price]] to Annie's parents, which frustrates Chris's wife, Nikki. Upon arriving in the United States, they initially stay with Chris and Nikki in Los Angeles, but eventually Nikki asks them to return to Louisville, where they get a negative reception from David's children. Despite David's past infidelity, drinking problems, and destitution, the couple got married. They live in [[Louisville, Kentucky]], although they think about moving back to Asia.<ref name=waiting>{{cite web | url=https://www.tlc.com/tv-shows/90-day-fiance/full-episodes/waiting-is-the-hardest-part | title=Waiting Is The Hardest Part | publisher=[[TLC (TV network)|TLC]]}}</ref>\n\n===Josh & Aika===\nJosh Batterson (43, from [[Mesa, Arizona]]) met Aika (36 from [[Quezon City]], [[Philippines]]). Aika enjoys living in the United States, but becomes frustrated when Josh pressures her to pursue a modeling career. She also struggles with skepticism from Josh's friend. Josh has previously been married and has two children. Despite  doubts about the future of their relationship due to Josh's reluctance to get surgery to reverse his [[vasectomy]] and allow him to have a child with Aika, who wants children, Josh & Aika got married in [[Las Vegas]].\n\n===Nicole & Azan===\nNicole Nafziger and Azan Tefou, who also appeared in season 4, are featured again in season 5. Nicole is a single mother from Florida and Azan is from Morocco. Nicole's father and stepmother agree to co-sponsor Azan's visa, as Nicole does not earn enough money to sponsor. Like season 4, Nicole goes to visit Azan in Morocco, but this time she brings her 2.5 year old daughter May. The couple argue frequently about cultural and lifestyle differences. Azan still struggles to trust Nicole after her previous infidelity. It is also revealed that Azan is currently unemployed and has received approximately $1300 from Nicole.\n\n==Season 6 cast==\n\n===Ashley & Jay===\nAshley Martson (33, from [[Mechanicsburg, Pennsylvania]]) met Jay Smith (20, from [[Port Maria, Jamaica]]), while she was vacationing at a resort for a friend's wedding. The pair connected via social media and continued to talk after her trip. Six months later, she returned to Jamaica and he proposed. Ashley has two young children from previous relationships and is expecting Jay to move to Pennsylvania to be with her.<ref name=season6>{{cite web | url=https://people.com/tv/90-day-fiance-season-six-cast/ | title=90 Day Fianc\u00e9 Is Back! Meet the Cast of the Sixth Season of TLC's Hit Reality Show | publisher=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref> They were married in Las Vegas in April 2018 after cancelling their planned wedding ceremony and reception in Pennsylvania due to racist comments that surfaced on their wedding website. Shortly after they returned home from Las Vegas, Ashley discovered Jay had made an account on [[Tinder (app)|Tinder]]. She filed for divorce on January 11, 2019, but then changed her mind a couple weeks later.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1007572/90-day-fiance-s-ashley-martson-files-for-divorce-from-jay-smith-then-changes-her-mind|title=Ashley Martson Files for Divorce From Jay Smith, Then Changes Mind|date=January 23, 2019|website=E! Online|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-17}}</ref>\n\n===Colt & Larissa===\nColt Johnson (33, from [[Las Vegas, Nevada]]) and Larissa Dos Santos Lima (31, from [[Minas Gerais, Brazil]]) met via an online dating website. Colt, a computer programmer who lives with his mother and three cats, flew to [[Mexico]] to meet Larissa for the first time and spent five days together. He subsequently flew to [[Rio de Janeiro]] to spend six more days with her. After eleven days total together, he proposed marriage and she is moving to Las Vegas to be with him. They were married in summer 2018 with the marriage lasting only about 6 months. On January 16, 2019, Larissa was charged with misdemeanor domestic violence. Colt subsequently filed for divorce on January 18, 2019.<ref name=season6/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/90-day-fiances-larissa-charged-with-domestic-violence/|title=90 Day Fiance\u2019s Larissa Dos Santos Lima Charged With Domestic Violence|date=2019-01-19|website=Us Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-17}}</ref> On February 17, 2019, Larissa revealed she had a new love interest on Instagram.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/90-day-fiances-colt-and-larissa-will-they-get-back-together/|title=90 Day Fiance's Colt and Larissa: Will They Get Back Together?|date=2019-03-02|website=Us Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-17}}</ref>\n\n===Jonathan & Fernanda===\nJonathan Rivera (32, from [[Lumberton, North Carolina]]) met Fernanda Flores (19, from [[Celaya, Mexico]]) while on a vacation in Mexico. The pair hit it off and, despite the age difference, began dating. Jonathan, a real estate broker, flew to Mexico to pick up Fernanda and they arrived in North Carolina to begin the 90 day visa process.<ref name=season6/> The couple married in May 2018. In January 2019 the couple announced they have separated, having not spoken since December 22. On March 12, 2019, Jon announced he has cancelled Fernanda's green card paperwork.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.intouchweekly.com/posts/90-day-fiance-jonathan-withdrew-fernandas-green-card-paperwork/|title='90 Day Fianc\u00e9' Star Jonathan Reveals He Withdrew Fernanda's Green Card Paperwork|date=2019-03-12|website=In Touch Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-17}}</ref>\n\n===Kalani & Asuelu===\nKalani Faagata (30, from [[Orange County, California]]) met Asuelu Pulaa (23, from [[Samoa]]) while she was on vacation in Samoa and he was working at the resort she was staying at. There, Kalani lost her virginity to Asuelu and Kalani became pregnant. Kalani gave birth to their son Oliver in January 2018. Asuelu is now making the move to California, a move that Kalani's family eyes with suspicion.<ref name=season6/> Kalani and Asuelu marry in a beautiful ceremony. In December 2018 it was announced that the couple is expecting their second son.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://starcasm.net/90-day-fiance-kalani-baby-bump-due-date/|title=90 DAY FIANCE Kalani shares baby bump photo, becomes pajama rights activist|last=Hawks|first=Asa|date=2019-02-22|website=starcasm.net|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-17}}</ref> Their second son Kennedy was born on May 7, 2019.\n\n===Eric & Leida===\nEric Rosenbrook (40, from [[Baraboo, Wisconsin]]) met Leida Margaretha Cohen (29, from [[Jakarta, Indonesia]]) on an international dating site. Eric is an avionics technician and former U.S. Marine and Leida claims to be  a model, actress, teacher, and medical school graduate from a wealthy family. Leida moved to Wisconsin and is wary that Eric pays child support. Likewise, Eric's family is questioning why Leida is giving up her affluent surroundings.<ref name=season6/> On January 20, 2019, police were called to Eric and Leida's home to investigate accusations of domestic abuse. Leida accused Eric of pulling her hair during a fight after she threatened that she was going to kill herself with a knife.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.intouchweekly.com/posts/90-day-fiance-eric-and-leida-address-domestic-incident/|title=90 Day Fianc\u00e9\u2019 Stars Eric and Leida Address Their Domestic Violence Incident: \u2018Everyone Is Calm|date=January 21, 2019|website= In Touch Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref> On February 8, 2019, Leida was granted a 4-year restraining order against Eric's daughter, Tasha Rosenbrook.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.intouchweekly.com/posts/90df-star-leida-gets-restraining-order-against-daughter-in-law/|title=\u201990 Day Fianc\u00e9\u2019 Star Leida Margaretha Granted 4-Year Restraining Order Against Husband Eric\u2019s Daughter|date=February 9, 2019|website= In Touch Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref>\n\n===Steven & Olga===\nSteven Frend (20, from [[Bowie, Maryland]]) met Olga Koshimbetova (20 from [[Voronezh, Russia]]) while Olga was staying in the United States for a summer. After dating for a few months, Olga became pregnant. Olga returned to her native Russia and in April 2018 had the baby boy named Alexander. The couple intends to raise the child in the United States. Steven traveled to Russia to attend to birth of his son after which he applied for K-1 visa for Olga. Olga's visa got approved on December 24, 2018.<ref name=season6/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://starcasm.net/90-day-fiance-steven-olga-k-1-visa-approved/|title=90 Day Fiance Steven announces Olga\u2019s K-1 visa approved on Christmas Eve|last=Hawks|first=Asa|date=2018-12-24|website=starcasm.net|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-17}}</ref>. Olga now is residing in Maryland with Steven.\n\n==Season 7 cast==\n\n===Emily & Sasha===\n\nEmily (29, from [[Portland, Oregon]]) met Sasha (32, from [[Moscow, Russia]]) after she moved to Russia for a job teaching English, and joined a gym where Sasha worked as a personal trainer.<ref name=\"parade1\">https://parade.com/946684/stephanieosmanski/90-day-fiance-season-7/</ref><ref name=\"parade2\">https://parade.com/946684/stephanieosmanski/90-day-fiance-season-7/</ref> She quickly fell for him and became pregnant, and they began their K1 journey, with Emily electing to have the baby in Russia so his father could be present at the birth. Their son David Aleksandrovich was born in November 2018. Emily will be Sasha\u2019s 3rd wife and baby David is his 3rd son. When the couple moves to the US, they face a constant  confrontation with Emily's sister who does not trust that Sasha has good intentions about Emily due to his two failed marriages. The couple married in a beautiful ceremony on Oregon beach and now is residing in Portland, OR where Emily got a job.\n\n===Anna & Mursel===\nAnna (38 from [[Bellevue, Nebraska]]) met Mursel (38, from [[Antalya, Turkey]]) on social media.<ref name=\"parade1\"/><ref name=\"parade2\"/> Despite their language barrier, their romance blossomed. Four months after her trip to Turkey, he proposed. Although Anna is looking forward to getting a happily ever after with Mursel, his family doesn\u2019t know about her three children, and would never approve of her choice to have children out of wedlock. Eventually Anna told Mursel that she can not marry him if his family does not know about her children.  After finding out about the children, his family requested Mursel to go back to Turkey and he left.  However, he returned to the US still within the 90 days of his K-1 visa and married Anna.\n\n===Michael & Juliana===\n\nMichael (42, from [[Greenwich, Connecticut]]) met Juliana (23, from [[Goiania, Brazil]]) at a yacht party in Croatia.<ref name=\"parade1\"/><ref name=\"parade2\"/> Michael travels a lot and lives a jetsetting lifestyle, and Juliana is working on launching her international modeling career. They immediately connected, fell in love, and applied for Juliana\u2019s tourist visa to come to America for the first time. Unfortunately, the couple was left devastated when her tourist visa to the US was denied. Her rejected application made Michael realize he wanted to spend his life with Juliana. He applied for her K1 Visa and looked forward to their future together in the US. However, his ex-wife and family has been concerned that Juliana has only seen pieces of his life, and is only in the relationship for a chance at a new life in America. Eventually Michael's ex-wife warms up to Juliana and becomes good friends with her. She even officiates Michael and Juliana's wedding.\n\n===Tania & Syngin===\n\nTania (29, from [[Colchester, Connecticut]]) met Syngin (29, from [[Cape Town, South Africa]]) after flying to South Africa to meet another man she connected with on a dating app.<ref name=\"parade1\"/><ref name=\"parade2\"/> When the original connection didn\u2019t work out, Tania struck up a flirty conversation with a bartender who ended up being Syngin and the rest is history. Following a memorable night together, Tania decided to stay in South Africa for four and a half months. The two are now ready to take the next step in their relationship and move to her home in Connecticut. However, when the couple begins living in a shed at her mother\u2019s house, they will realize their differences and question their future together. During the 90 days of Syngin's K-1 visa, Tania had to leave on a business trip to Costa Rica for a month which brought a lot of tension between then.  However, eventually the couple went on to marry.\n\n===Robert & Anny===\n\nRobert (41, from [[Winter Park, Florida]]) and Anny (31, from [[Santiago, Dominican Republic]]) talked every day for six months until Robert took a cruise with a stop in the Dominican Republic.<ref name=\"parade1\"/><ref name=\"parade2\"/> After eight hours together, Robert proposed to Anny and applied for her K1 Visa. Although Robert sees a future with Anny, his full-time job and responsibilities as a single father  of seven children have prevented him from purchasing an engagement ring and returning to the Dominican Republic to visit his fianc\u00e9. Despite a lot of negative interference from the grandmother of one of Robert's sons, Bryson, the couple got married. They are now expecting their first child together.\n\n===Blake & Jasmin===\n\nBlake (29, from [[Los Angeles, California]]) connected with Jasmin (27, from [[Helsinki, Finland]]) online.<ref name=\"parade1\"/><ref name=\"parade2\"/> After taking a trip to Finland to meet Jasmin, the couple entered into an exclusive relationship, and during his second visit, he proposed. While Blake believes he and Jasmin are destined to be together, his friends and family can\u2019t ignore the fact that Jasmin\u2019s sister lives nearby after winning the green card lottery. Although Blake is in love, they suspect Jasmin could be using him to reunite with her sister. Jasmin does not show any interest in Blake's music. Blake's parents do not allow the couple to live together until they are married, so Jasmin has to live with Blake's parents, while he lives with his friends. Eventually they marry.\n\n===Mike & Natalie===\n\nMike (34, from [[Sequim, Washington]]) met Natalie (35, from [[Kyiv, Ukraine]]) after Mike's best friend and Ukrainian wife played matchmaker, introducing Mike to the wife's best friend, Natalie, and the two started chatting online.<ref name=\"parade1\"/><ref name=\"parade2\"/> Mike flew to Ukraine to meet Natalie in person and by the end of the trip, he was sold that she was the one. On a second trip meeting each other in Paris, Mike proposed in front of the Eiffel Tower. They have some pretty big differences - Natalie\u2019s vegetarian and Mike is not, Natalie is religious and Mike believes in aliens - but mostly, Mike is hoping that her being a city girl and him living a more rustic lifestyle won\u2019t get in the way of their relationship growing. After Natalie's K1 visa got delayed, Mike flew to Kyiv to spend some time with Natalie.  However, their relationship took a bad turn during that visit.  Natalie is still awaiting her visa.\n\n===Angela & Michael===\nAngela (53, from [[Hazlehurst, Georgia]]) and Michael (31, from [[Lagos, Nigeria]]) are returning from Seasons 1 and 2 of <em>90 Day Fianc\u00e9: Before the 90 Days</em>.<ref name=\"parade1\"/><ref name=\"parade2\"/> After initially breaking up at the end of Season 1, they reunited Season 2. The reunion has since been a rollercoaster filled with lies, numerous arguments, financial theft, and probable infertility on Angela's part due to her age. Nonetheless, the couple celebrated an engagement party thrown by his family in Nigeria, and are seeking a K1 for Michael so they can get married in the United States in front of her mother. However, bad news come for the couple when Michael's visa is about to be denied.  Angela flies to Nigeria and faces a pressure from Michael's family to get married in Nigeria as well as negativity of Michael's friends.  She leaves for the US without marrying Michael.  They are still awaiting the final decision on Michael's visa.\n\n==Episodes==\n===Series overview===\n{{Series overview\n| color1       = #B30713\n| link1        = #Season 1 (2014)\n| episodes1    = 6\n| start1       = {{Start date|2014|1|12}}\n| end1         = {{End date|2014|2|23}}\n\n| color2       = #FF69B4\n| link2        = #Season 2 (2014)\n| episodes2    = 12\n| start2       = {{Start date|2014|10|19}}\n| end2         = {{End date|2014|12|28}}\n\n| color3       = #689CCF\n| link3        = #Season 3 (2015)\n| episodes3    = 12\n| start3       = {{Start date|2015|10|11}}\n| end3         = {{End date|2015|12|6}}\n\n| color4       = #C89CCF\n| link4        = #Season 4 (2016)\n| episodes4    = 14\n| start4       = {{Start date|2016|9|11}}\n| end4         = {{End date|2016|11|20}}\n\n| color5       = #006600\n| link5        = #Season 5 (2017)\n| episodes5    = 13\n| start5       = {{Start date|2017|10|8}}\n| end5         = {{End date|2017|12|18}}\n\n| color6       = #FBEC5C\n| link6        = #Season 6 (2018)\n| episodes6    = 13\n| start6       = {{Start date|2018|10|21}}\n| end6         = {{End date|2019|01|13}}\n\n| color7       = #339BE9\n| link7        = #Season 7 (2019)\n| episodes7    = 15\n| start7       = {{Start date|2019|11|3}}\n| end7         = {{End date|2020|02|17}}\n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2014)===\n{{Episode table |background=#B30713 |overall=5 |season=5 |title=40 |director=25 |airdate=25 |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = I Got My Visa!\n| DirectedBy      = Jessica Hernandez\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|1|12}}\n| ShortSummary    = Four women come to the US to live with their American fiances using a unique 90 da